Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.41,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0015,,{\blur3}I have a big gun, I took it from my Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:21.79,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Sick with Justice, I just wanna feel you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.02,0:00:25.20,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'm your angel, only a ring away...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.55,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You make me violate you, no matter who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:38.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's all up to you, no one lives forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Been burn in the hell, by all those pigs out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:45.53,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's always been hell, from when I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:48.72,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}They make me violate them, no matter who they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:52.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fs79}Get down on your knees! Get a good head on your shoulders!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:55.69,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}If it's for your guys, go to the end of the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:59.00,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Do what you think, give it with dedication...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:02.27,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'll put out your misery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:05.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You made a mess! For Christ sakes, this rotten world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:09.10,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Shit out of luck! Go with my vision!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:12.54,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Light up the fire! Right on the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.54,0:01:15.90,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:24.48,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.59,0:01:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over this past year, I've woken up\Nwith hangovers in the following places...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.90,0:01:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes I might wake up in the\Ncabin aboard the torpedo boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.26,0:01:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and sometimes the office\Nof a pirating company...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.90,0:01:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but generally, this is my place of rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.67,0:01:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cheap hotel room looking\Ndown over downtown Roanapur.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time in a year, I'm leaving\Nthis country for a far away location.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.75,0:02:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A place that is too far removed\Nfrom the current me. That country...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.06,0:02:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that you, Rock? Happy New Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.70,0:02:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's hard to get\Ninto that mood here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing but the\NChinese setting off fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.94,0:02:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Everything's decorated\Nnicely for the new year here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.74,0:02:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How's Revy doing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All she does is complain. She didn't\Nlike the Tokarev she was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.51,0:02:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was in a bad mood\Nover that yesterday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.88,0:02:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You sure are a lady's man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She went with you because she{\i0}\N{\i1}was worried about you, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.29,0:02:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I should be going now.\NI'll call you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.19,0:02:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting to snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It snows worse in New York,\Nbut still, this is nostalgic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.33,0:02:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been ages since I last saw snow.\NEver since I left that city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How do you like Japan?\N- I've been hit on by a few guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I talk back, they make a face\Nand repeat the word "gaijin".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.38,0:03:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This country pisses me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.68,0:03:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, today, we meet face to\Nface for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming from so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.49,0:03:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These guys are my men.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.02,0:03:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, how shall I address you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.86,0:03:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just Balalaika is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.90,0:03:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been briefed by Laptev.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been eager to set up\Nbase in Tokyo for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.34,0:03:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do appreciate your assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.41,0:03:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you join forces with us,\Nthere'll be nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you've heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Kanto Peace Council is\Nmaking an effort to keep foreigners out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Laptev from Russia is one example\Nof someone who was thrown out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.36,0:03:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was thinking... We could\Nreach out a helping hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't the Washimine\Nclan a part of the Council?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can only go so far in\Nmeeting their call to duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've gone to great lengths to fulfill\Nour obligation to the Kousa clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I think we've done a\Nlot for the Peace Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.65,0:04:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't stay at the bottom of the\Npile forever, simply outta obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.25,0:04:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our interests are mutually\Nbeneficial, Mr. Bando.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.02,0:04:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You expand your reach with our help...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.76,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...while we will set up a new\Nenterprise in this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.40,0:04:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're quick to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.17,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you suppress the Kousa\Nclan with your power...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.53,0:04:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then the Peace Council cannot\Nafford to go against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our emblem will gain power.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.47,0:04:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that among the Russians,\Nyou're most used to being in a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.15,0:04:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're concerned about our forces?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.95,0:04:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our forces are nothing\Nlike those in this nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.92,0:04:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We are a military force.\N- Let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.89,0:05:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's me. Are you in position?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- {\i1}Very well.{\i0}\N- Mr. Interpreter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.17,0:05:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's now speaking in Russian.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.20,0:05:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perfect. Go ahead and begin.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start things off, we've blown up one\Nof the clubs owned by the Kousa clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.62,0:05:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blown up?! You idiot!\NWhat are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.92,0:05:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Intimidation with handguns\Namounts to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.02,0:05:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will make our strength very\Nclear with our first strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how Hotel Moscow\Nmakes a show of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will decimate anything... that\Nstands in our way, you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.20,0:05:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we have come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me. It's one hell of a firework\Nto start off the Washimine clan's fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.11,0:05:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've taken a liking to you, Miss Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All those yakuza guys were...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.09,0:06:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...paralyzed with fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a little much to return to,\Nafter being away for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.99,0:06:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish they wouldn't turn my\Ncountry into a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.29,0:06:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sis was in a really good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.86,0:06:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There hasn't been a big fight\Nin Roanapur lately, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:15.54,Black Lagoon Reserved,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(1156,749)}RESE{\c&H235037&}RVED
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the type to give up fucking if\Nthere's a war to be fought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.54,0:06:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- There's something wrong with her.\N- She's a war maniac.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.84,0:06:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She left a few important\Nscrews back in Afghanistan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.21,0:06:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Rock. What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. They have a fair up.\NIt's for the new year season.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.02,0:06:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's a carnival. Looks\Nlike fun. Hey, driver!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see any Ferris wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find them at a\Ntraditional Japanese fair, Revy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Here you go!\N- Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's my third one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're living up to\Nthe name of Two-Hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:06:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that right.\NWho do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.21,0:07:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Miss Rebecca. Just give me a gun\Nand I'll show you why I'm the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my fourth. It's a shame\NI don't have my Cutlass.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could close this shop\Ndown in three seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.32,0:07:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, this is the hardest country\Nin the world to have a gunfight in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.83,0:07:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you can't bribe the\Ncops here like in Roanapur.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.06,0:07:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be thrown in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.74,0:07:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You remembering something?\N- Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.57,0:07:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean,\N"Like what?" This is your country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.01,0:07:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have anyone?\NYou know. Like, family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like you were born\Nfrom the crotch of a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.78,0:07:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought snoops weren't well liked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. Just wondering\Nwhat you were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You looked like you were deep\Nin thought about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.63,0:07:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the time you pulled\Na gun on me, on that boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.50,0:07:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a year has already passed. Time flies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.97,0:07:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:08:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a place I knew well,\Nbut I feel like I don't know it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My family doesn't get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.41,0:08:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My older brother turned out\Nwell and got a government job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.48,0:08:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I got into college a year late\Nand ended up in a normal company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't expect much of me.\NI guess they really didn't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.69,0:08:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your parents are alive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.79,0:08:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least contact them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't been arrested yet.\NThis is your only chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.03,0:08:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep this up, one day you'll\Nnever be able to see them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.34,0:08:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From our point of view, yours is a normal\Nhome. Isn't it worth going home to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got this far without stealing or killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.38,0:08:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't misunderstand me. I'm just saying\Nyou should at least go give them a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't say I'm really normal. Hanging\Naround you guys is clear proof of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.80,0:09:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.33,0:09:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! One more and I get the top score!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! I bet it's weighed down!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:09:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.91,0:09:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Hey, Rock!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.72,0:09:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, she says she scored enough points\Nfor first place, so give her the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way. She can't cheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.82,0:09:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says it doesn't count. Because\Nyou poked it and pushed it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You bastard! What\Nthe fuck?! Bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.93,0:09:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna take this\Nkinda crap, you dickweed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.03,0:09:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What the hell?! Speak Japanese!\N- What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.07,0:09:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You just cussed at me, didn't you?!\N- What the hell are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.37,0:09:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Revy, cut it out!\N- Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you! We're in\NJapan! Speak Japanese!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.75,0:09:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss customer. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.59,0:10:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the middle of the new year's\Nweek. Why don't we all just have fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.46,0:10:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please lay your aggression aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy! Let's go! We're being a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock, baby. Are you taking his side?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna be unreasonable,\NI have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.44,0:10:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is short, so we'd all like to\Njust enjoy what we have left of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.55,0:10:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had your fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so please take advantage\Nof this opportunity to save face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.79,0:10:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revy! Let it go, Revy! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.73,0:10:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Um, sweet sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.63,0:10:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you join me for some sweet sake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.17,0:10:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's chilly, so rather than\Nstanding around in the cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who the fuck are you?\N- Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:11:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I agree. I prefer not to\Nfight, so let's do it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how did we end up like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.45,0:11:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. There's nothing to gain\Nfrom making a big scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not even in the mood any more.\NLost the buzz.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.66,0:11:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well thank God Almighty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.23,0:11:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really glad things calmed down, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.83,0:11:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, I'm sorry!\N- Oh, please go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.24,0:11:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um... Then sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.44,0:11:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a student.\NOr are you a vendor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.58,0:11:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yes. They're both correct.\NMy father was, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was a vendor. That man...\NGinji is like my father's student.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's an argument here,\Neveryone goes to Ginji.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.69,0:11:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's big, right? His body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.26,0:11:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before he realized it, he was\Nlike the arbitrator of Takamachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.47,0:11:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.57,0:11:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would help close shop today\Nafter my college entrance exam classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that was a little shock to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's ultra-short tempered to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.98,0:12:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just glad she didn't\Nend up causing a big scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.18,0:12:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Is she Japanese?\N- Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's Chinese-American. How should\NI put it... She works with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.52,0:12:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to translate for a Russian,\Nand she came with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An international occupation\Nis very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. It's a small company and\Nwe're always dealing with trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot of hard work,\Nand it's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.81,0:12:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's dangerous?\N- Ah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.08,0:12:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.65,0:12:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.38,0:12:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you laughing at, asshole?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.75,0:12:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss. You're not a\Ndecent woman, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.23,0:12:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There. Those eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those aren't good eyes.\NThose are the eyes of a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.80,0:13:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no fucking idea what\Nyou just said, but... I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.14,0:13:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the same kind as me. You stink\Nof blood and guts. A smell I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.58,0:13:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's getting cold. Miss, sitting\Nout here isn't good for your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.38,0:13:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's how we met.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, by the way, what's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. It's Yukio. Yuki, as in snow,\Nand O, as in sandal straps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That day...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.13,0:13:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still didn't know just how{\i0}\N{\i1}powerful the underground world is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0230 hours. We have assaulted\Na Kousa clan office.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:13:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed result. Twelve kills,\Nno fatalities, no casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.43,0:14:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All men left the scene by 0237 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.10,0:14:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I have them prepare Russian tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.60,0:14:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't want to make a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.44,0:14:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Then some toast?\N- Would you like some, Sergeant?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.34,0:14:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't skip breakfast,\NSergeant. It's not healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the situation with\Npolice force intervention?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.81,0:14:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. They closed off\Nthe scene at 0305 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.08,0:14:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're on heightened security status.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a member of the\NWashimine clan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...transcribe their\Nwireless communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.42,0:14:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must wait for Rock's\Ntranslation for the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.96,0:14:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reliability of information\Ncould mean life or death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.29,0:14:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Have him translate it immediately.\N- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.36,0:14:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I would expect from you, Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.93,0:14:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see why Boss\NSlevenin acknowledges you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.84,0:14:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's ass do you think\NI'm wiping, Vasily?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've disgraced the reputation\Nof the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't even take control\Nof a single playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.82,0:14:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to wrap up the operation\Nhere and get back to Roanapur.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.92,0:15:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That place is full of gunpowder,\Nso I can't leave it unattended for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye. I'll see you in six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't overstep your\Nboundaries, Balalaika!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.23,0:15:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back in Moscow, I'm one\Nof the respected bosses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.40,0:15:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.33,0:15:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to remember those who rose\Nup using money instead of skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I better write your name down on\Na dollar bill so I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.67,0:15:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize, you ex-military bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.88,0:15:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm warning you. There are two\Nthings in this world I can't stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.95,0:15:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One is cold blintzes, and the other\Nis dimwitted ex-KGB shit heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Live with your head low so\Nthe bullets don't hit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.54,0:15:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, kids nowadays would\Nrather have video games than these.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much longer do you\Nplan on enduring this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the true job of a vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot better than\Nselling drugs or women.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.97,0:16:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you implying that I\Ndo this because I like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.47,0:16:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the old man died, he left us this\Ngroup that can barely get tribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason we've\Ncome this far is because...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the old man and the Kousa clan's\Nlast head took each other as brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.75,0:16:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now with that gone, those guys haven't\Nlet anyone take the head of our group...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.02,0:16:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...even now, three years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.99,0:16:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the only ones left with any\Nsense of obligation to the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.20,0:16:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He took care of me when I\Ncame from the Kansai region.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.27,0:16:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you see, we've gotta do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.78,0:17:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gin-boy. You said that dealing with\Nlow-lifes was a shame upon the yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.28,0:17:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that only matters if we have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.85,0:17:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what the old man said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.96,0:17:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pulling off a big job right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Joining up with Russians to\Ntake out the guys above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss. Do you realize what you're saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.37,0:17:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They tried to take us out first!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.20,0:17:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the Russians are Russians,\Nno matter how you cut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have a shred of honor. So we\Nneed to stay in control of certain areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.85,0:17:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to take it up again.\NThat white scabbard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.89,0:17:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name that still puts fear into\Nall yakuza: Man-slayer Ginji.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.16,0:17:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you show that to me once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.96,0:18:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss. I'm grateful that you're\Nlooking after the young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.30,0:18:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also understand what\Nyou're saying. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.51,0:18:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you're suggesting now\Ndoesn't bear a shred of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.34,0:18:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I held the white scabbard for the\Nold man, it was because he had that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.05,0:18:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess that's that. I'll come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those Russians...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did they bring their own interpreter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.49,0:18:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah they did.\N- What kinda guy is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.03,0:18:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a young guy with a pretty,\Nbut naughty, girl by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't look like anything\Nmore than a normal guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.24,0:18:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had to make an analogy, he's like\Na bird that arrives at the doorstep...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.84,0:18:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...with soup, onions, and even\Nthe pot to cook himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.75,0:18:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I won't be too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.32,0:18:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Later.\N- Shoo. Hurry up and go. Shoo, shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.56,0:19:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for you, but not for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.40,0:19:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just until I finish drinking this.\NAfter that I'm leaving, Partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.78,0:19:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sky looks the same\Nno matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.98,0:19:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, or in Mott Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You God damn brats!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.76,0:19:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna shoot each other up,\Nthen head on out to Lebanon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.16,0:19:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, so you're a\Nreal gunman, aren't ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.33,0:19:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at this sorry excuse for a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.06,0:19:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, brats! Now watch those cans\Nwe got lined up there, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bang! Bang! Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.01,0:19:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wow!\N- That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Like magic!\N- Just like Annie Oakley, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.94,0:19:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack McCall!\NI'm here to avenge Wild Bill!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.68,0:19:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you defeat me, the\Nincredible Jane? Now, come at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.36,0:20:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, wait a sec! No,\Nno, you got it all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.26,0:20:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only place you'll see people go down\Nlike that is in the movies or on TV shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. I n reality, you suddenly lose\Nall your strength. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like everything below your knees\Ndisappears, and your feet stagger...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and unable to position yourself,\Nyou go down head first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.34,0:20:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you how it happens. You.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.43,0:20:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, that's not\Nvery cool looking, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.90,0:20:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always like this when you die.\NIt's really not that cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What are you doing?\N- How long have you been watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since about the time you charged\Ninto the Deadwood saloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.71,0:20:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed the scenario\Nchanged part way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.81,0:21:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calamity Jane didn't die at that location.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- My toy pistol!\N- Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.36,0:21:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ow, ow!\N- You tell Dutch or Benny about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.46,0:21:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and I'll cut off your balls\Nand pole and feed them to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.76,0:21:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't! I won't say a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.76,0:21:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So? Were you able to meet your folks?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.60,0:21:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I did go to the house,\Nbut I wasn't able to see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.14,0:21:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.51,0:21:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing. But we still have\Na few more days here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.78,0:21:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why doesn't he go home?{\i0}\N{\i1}This place suits him so perfectly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.93,0:21:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is it with this guy?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:18.56,Black Lagoon Next Episode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur10\pos(980,916)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.33,0:23:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss! The Russians aren't holding back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.80,0:23:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've b-blown something up\Nagain today!
